The paper deals with distributed epistemic gossip protocols, which involve communication and knowledge sharing among agents. This falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of epistemic logic in analyzing these protocols, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also touches upon game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA) in the context of gossip protocols.
